# api-endpoints

The API implements specialized endpoints for meeting and document management with the following key business logic components:

## Meeting Signal Processing
Path: /api/v1/meetings/
Importance Score: 85
- Extracts structured signals from meeting content:
  - Decisions
  - Action items
  - Blockers
  - Risks
  - Ideas
- Maintains signal relationships across meetings
- Tracks signal evolution states (draft, active, archived)
- Associates signals with DIKW hierarchy levels

## Document Knowledge Graph
Path: /api/v1/documents/
Importance Score: 80
- Creates semantic relationships between documents
- Manages document signal extraction pipeline
- Links documents to related meetings and tickets
- Tracks document knowledge state transitions

## Signal Feedback Loop
Path: /api/v1/signals/
Importance Score: 75
- Implements signal confidence scoring system
- Manages signal approval workflows
- Tracks signal usage patterns
- Updates signal relevance based on user interactions

## DIKW Transformation API
Path: /api/v1/dikw/
Importance Score: 90
- Handles promotion of content through DIKW levels
- Manages knowledge item relationships
- Processes signal synthesis requests
- Controls knowledge item lifecycle states

## Career Development Integration
Path: /api/v1/career/
Importance Score: 70
- Links signals to skill development evidence
- Tracks career progression through signal patterns
- Maps knowledge items to career competencies
- Manages career insight generation

